cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.ST, cs.NA, cs.SI 

The paper proposes a framework for blind source separation, which is a problem in machine learning and signal processing. The use of Copula as a tool for modeling dependency structure suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves statistical inference and estimation, which are topics in cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.ST (Statistics). The use of Copula may also suggest the paper belongs to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
